# Growth Forge — GTM Factory

- Next.js App Router + React + TypeScript + Tailwind + Framer Motion
- `@cursor/sdk` for real agent orchestration (parallel agents, not fictional subagent delegation)
- Generative UI: the ad creative IS the interface during Distribute (~80% of screen)
- Dark theme: `#0A0A0F` background, amber glows, minimal chrome
- Ambient agent activity: CSS text-shadow pulse, hue-rotate shimmer — NOT progress bars or agent cards
- Framer Motion: AnimatePresence for version morph, layout animations
- Mobile-first: swipe for version comparison, hold for distribution-gate overlay
- DEMO_MODE=true on Vercel (theatrical SSE). DEMO_MODE=false locally for real SDK
- GTM stations: Scope → Distribute → Reach out
  - Scope = ICP + buying signals + channel mix + audience count
  - Distribute = work assigned across agents; test/iterate until ≥3% CTR gate
  - Reach out = multi-touch cadence (Meta + email + LinkedIn) with replies feeding back
- One primary action per screen (Scope it / Distribute the work / Approve → plan reach-out / Send it)
- Keep UI calm — output-first, chrome-last
- Routes: `/` landing, `/forge` interactive factory
- API: `POST /api/campaign` with `stage: "scope" | "distribute"`
